		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>We demonstrate in this paper how certain forms of rule-based knowledge can be used to prestructure a neural network of normalized basis functions and give a probabilistic interpretation of the network architecture. We describe several ways to assure that rule-based knowledge is preserved during training and present a method for complexity reduction that tries to minimize the number of rules and the number of conjuncts. After training the refined rules are extracted and analyzed.</p>
